The government's decision:

The Government Medical and Super Speciality Hospital, Nagpur is being granted administrative sanction for procurement of machinery and equipment for patient care as well as for various visits and training for undergraduate and postgraduate students, as well as for research and patient screening from the State Plan Grant of Rs.
1) This administrative approval is being made from the funds available under the State Plan or from the provision approved by the Supplementary Demand during the 2023-24 year.
2) The Government issued a "Manual of Procedure for Office Procurement to be carried out by the Government Department" in this regard by the Department of Industries, Power and Labour.
